demoText.heading: Intro
demoText.start: To learn how the game works, play a demo
demoText.finish: You can play this demo again or ask the research assistant any questions. Good luck!

popovers.blueButton: Each round, you can guess blue
popovers.correct: The correct answer will be displayed in the center after you make your choice.
popovers.incorrect: The correct answer will be displayed in the center after you make your choice.

popovers.yellowButton: Sometimes, yellow will be correct more often

popovers.blueButton: And sometimes blue will be correct more often
popovers.correct: By considering which color has been correct more often in the past, you can build a feeling of which color is more likely to be correct in the future.
popovers.incorrect: By considering which color has been correct more often in the past, you can build a feeling of which color is more likely to be correct in the future.

popovers.pointsBar: Each time you answer correctly, your points increase.

popovers.advice: You will also get advice, represented by the figure
Your advisor recommends yellow for 25 points

popovers.advisorBar: Your advisor is trying to get you to score a certain amount of points. These goals are randomly generated each game.
So, depending on their goals, the advisor might try to help you or to hurt you.
In the game, you will not be able to see your advisor's goals. Instead, you will have to guess if their advice is good or bad.
